     Aug. 13 (Bloomberg) -- Whirlpool Corp. said it agreed to
take a majority stake in Hefei Rongshida Sanyo Electric Co. for
about $552 million.  Whirlpool, based in  Benton Harbor ,  Michigan , will purchase
shares from Sanyo Electric Co. and buy new Hefei Sanyo shares
via a private placement, the company said today in a statement.
The transaction is expected to be completed by the end of 2014.  To contact the reporter on this story:
